I have manually configured a Fisheye repository to index everything from the Subversion root.  This has caused the instructions on the Fisheye main page to be incorrect:

{noformat}
This project is using Subversion. You may check out the source code by running:
 svn checkout /all/trunk all --username sysadmin
{noformat}

This was for a http host. For a https host, it causes a http:// URL to be used (the Fisheye base URL is correctly set to https).
